Pathology of Radicular cyst:
A radicular cyst arises from the periodontalligament usually secondary to low-grade inflammation andinfection. It therefore occurs most commonly at the apex of anonvital tooth. In addition to caries, it can also result fromtrauma. These two mechanisms may lead to necrosis of thepulp cavity and may subsequently spread to the tooth apex,with development of a periapical granuloma or periapical
abscess. This leads secondary to the formation of aradicular cyst.
